SIMPLE: sundowner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sundowner
<hw>Sun"down`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tramp or
vagabond in the Australian bush; -- so called from his coming to sheep
stations at sunset of ask for supper and a bed, when it is too late to
work; -- called also <altname>traveler</altname> and
<altname>swagman</altname> (but not all <xex>swagmen</xex> are
<ex>sundowners</ex>).</def></p>

<p><q><qex>Sundowners</qex>, -- men who loaf about till sunset, and then
come in with the demand for unrefusable rations.</q> <rj><qau>Francis
Adams.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sun-dried</ent>⟦br⟧
